every chocoholics dream cake it really doesn t get much better
ferrero rocher chocolates and chopped toasted hazelnuts to decorate
don t forget you can add these ingredients to your woolworths shopping list
grease a 22cm springform cake pan and line the base and sides with baking
crumble brownie into the bottom of the pan and press to form a firm base if
needed add a little butter to bring the base together refrigerate until
place cream and sugar in a saucepan over medium heat and stir to dissolve the
meanwhile soak gelatine in cold water for 5 minutes to soften
place chocolate in a food processor and whiz until finely chopped add the hot
cream mixture and whiz until melted and smooth squeeze water from the
gelatine then add the eggwhites and gelatine and whiz to combine add cream
cheese and frangelico if using whiz until very smooth pour mixture over
base and refrigerate for 4 hours or until firmly set
when ready to serve make the icing place butter and icing sugar in the bowl
of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment beat until thick and pale
beat in cocoa until combined gently fold in sour cream
remove cake from pan and place on a serving plate using a palette knife
spread icing over and decorate with hazelnuts and ferrero rocher chocolates
